profile_positions.description:
Connecting the Netherlands and the EU in the field of animal health & welfare, plant health & plant protection products, safe & sustainable food production and veterinary & phytosanitary trade. 

This included such activities as:
• succesfully managing the lobby for NL candidate running for the EFSA Board (2014) and for a EP position on the Plant Health Regulation which was essential in preserving a risk based approach for EU imports of flowers, plants, fruit, vegetables and breeding material from third countries (2014);
• representing NL in Council Attache Meetings on European Commission legislative proposals for the Official Controls, Animal Health, Plant Health, Cloning of Animals, Food of Cloned Animals, Genetically Modified Organisms and Financial Regulations (2013-2017);
• managing NL Presidency of the Council of the EU in the first half of 2016 for the above mentioned policy domains including:
- preparing Dutch government officials for NL Presidency of the Council in 2016 (2015);
- planning and organising Council Working Groups and Council Attache meetings (2015-2016);
- chairing Council Attache Meetings on a.o. Genetically Modified Organisms, Sustainable Use of Plant Protection Products and Antimicrobial Resistance (2016);
- succesfully influencing the decision making process towards the establishment of the EU Animal Welfare Platform and towards adoption of Council Conclusions on Sustainable Use of Plant Protection Products and Antimicrobial Resistance (2016);
• initiating, organising and hosting a member state meeting on Insects for Feed (2015) and a conference on the Future of Food in the EU together with the Maltese and Slovakian Trio-Presidency colleagues (2017);
• liaising with the Council Secretariat, EU member states, the Cabinet of Commissioner Andriukaitis, DG SANTE, the European Parliament and EU lobbyists (2013-2017).
